        "detail": {
          "issue": "Potential type safety risk when parsing the input string. The `JSON.parse` method does not validate the structure of the parsed JSON, which could lead to incorrect type assignments."
        },
        "root": "sha256:f71e2d580e8a597ab5dc6d476a6e5ef6e286ab8b36fb3b9d35aa82ca7b0c585b"
      },
      {
        "type": "patch_proposed",
        "at": "2026-04-26T00:00:07.000Z",
        "detail": {
          "patch": "Use a try-catch block to handle potential JSON parsing errors and validate the structure of the parsed JSON before casting it to the Result type.\n\n```typescript\nexport function parseResult(input: string): Result | null {\n  try {\n    const result = JSON.parse(input);\n    if (typeof result === 'object' && 'ok' in result && 'value' in result) {\n      return result as Result;\n    } else {\n      throw new Error('Parsed JSON does not match the Result type structure');\n    }\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('Failed to parse input:', error);\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n```\n"
        },
        "root": "sha256:b8e59b5a2a3193dfa89ce6b6ee9c14c515eb74e91014263054d6926228e8fea7"
      },
